HIV infection has now become a chronic disease with a good life expectancy 
thanks to antiretrovirals. The mortality currently is attributed to other 
pathologies in particular cardiovascular because of the inflammation and the 
side effects of the drugs. All arteries can be damaged in HIV, especially the 
aorta, with several types of lesions which can be occlusive, aneurysmal, 
